                     <origDate notBefore="1711" notAfter="1716">Yoḥannǝs is mentioned as the
                        Patriarch (John XVI, Patriarch of Alexandria in 1676-1718) and Marqos as the
                        Metropolitan (Marqos IV was Metropolitan of Ethiopia in 1689-1716) (<locus target="#34rb">34rb</locus>, 35ra, etc.), Yosṭos (r. 1711-16) is
                        mentioned as the reigning king (<locus target="#22ra">22ra</locus>, 35va,
                        46ra).</origDate>
                  </origin>
               <provenance>Zämädä Māryām was the donor according to
                     Additio 3. Supplication formulas also mention Takla Mikāʾel, Gabra Krǝstos,
                     Gabra Hǝywät, Za-Walda Māryām, Walatta Mikāʾel, Walatta Māryām, Walatta
                     Yoḥannǝs, Walatta Madḫǝn and Walatta Kidān (s. 64vb, 69ra, 79ra, etc.).</provenance></history>
